 data-bs-target=3D"#nav_scrollspy"><div id=3D"pgtype-ref"><div class=3D"obj=
ect_ref"><span id=3D"mw_d97d5eca-4dc4-49cf-ae10-90d7516289d0" class=3D"anch=
or_target"></span><h1 class=3D"r2023b notranslate" itemprop=3D"title">slice=
Viewer</h1><div class=3D"doc_topic_desc"><div class=3D"purpose_container"><=
p itemprop=3D"purpose" class=3D"add_margin_0">Browse image slices</p><p cla=
ss=3D"add_margin_0 add_clear_left"><em>Since R2019b</em></p><div class=3D"s=
witch mwToggle0"><a id=3D"expandAllPage">expand all in page</a></div></div>=
</div><div class=3D"refsummary" itemprop=3D"content"><h2 id=3D"mw_4ff06ab8-=
9b0a-43a0-90bc-7eacc137e41b">Description</h2>
    <div class=3D"shortsummary"><p>A <code class=3D"object">sliceViewer</co=
de> object displays individual slices of grayscale and
      RGB volumes. You can control which slice to display by using a slider=
.</p></div>
    <p>When it opens, the <code class=3D"object">sliceViewer</code> object =
displays the middle image in the
      stack in the direction specified by <code class=3D"literal">sliceDire=
ction</code>. Use the slider to
      navigate through the volume and view individual slices.</p>
    <div class=3D"informalfigure"><div id=3D"d126e305961" class=3D"mediaobj=
ect"><p><img src=3D"https://ww2.mathworks.cn/help/releases/R2023b/images/re=
f/slice_viewer_ref.png" height=3D"417" width=3D"405"></p></div></div>
    <p>The <code class=3D"object">sliceViewer</code> object supports proper=
ties, object functions, and events
      that you can use to customize its appearance and functioning. The <co=
de class=3D"object">sliceViewer</code>
      object can send notifications when certain events occur, such as the =
slider moving. For more
      information, see <a href=3D"https://ww2.mathworks.cn/help/releases/R2=
023b/images/ref/sliceviewer.html#mw_5cc89f18-2625-4074-a26d-963dd2dcf630" c=
lass=3D"intrnllnk">Events</a>.</p>
    <div class=3D"alert alert-info"><span id=3D"mw_ae4ccb45-1605-414b-b9dd-=
ec6721205bfb" class=3D"anchor_target"></span><span class=3D"alert_icon icon=
-alert-info-reverse"></span><p class=3D"alert_heading"><strong>Note</strong=
></p><p>By default, clicking and dragging the mouse in the slice displayed =
interactively changes
        their brightness and contrast, a technique called <em class=3D"firs=
tterm">window/level</em>.
        Dragging the mouse horizontally from left to right changes the cont=
rast. Dragging the mouse
        vertically up and down changes the brightness. Holding down the <st=
rong class=3D"keycap">Ctrl</strong> key
        when clicking and dragging the mouse accelerates changes. Holding d=
own the
          <strong class=3D"keycap">Shift</strong> key while clicking and dr=
agging the mouse slows the rate of change.
        Press these keys before clicking and dragging. To control this beha=
vior, use the <a href=3D"https://ww2.mathworks.cn/help/releases/R2023b/imag=
es/ref/sliceviewer.html#mw_0ba6b3fe-682d-404d-ab9f-33ac3750bcde" class=3D"i=
ntrnllnk">DisplayRangeInteraction</a> property.</p></div>
  </div><div id=3D"mw_70f6ca8d-06b7-4e85-b6d2-bf12ee95dad1_div" class=3D"re=
f_sect createobject"><h2 id=3D"mw_70f6ca8d-06b7-4e85-b6d2-bf12ee95dad1">Cre=
ation</h2><div id=3D"mw_3c59f330-0a53-4e0d-96a5-d908f1680c29_div" class=3D"=
refsect2 description"><h3 id=3D"mw_3c59f330-0a53-4e0d-96a5-d908f1680c29">De=
scription</h3><div class=3D"description_module"><div class=3D"description_e=
lement"><p class=3D"syntax_example"><a href=3D"https://ww2.mathworks.cn/hel=
p/releases/R2023b/images/ref/sliceviewer.html#mw_303c0e03-12d6-4bb8-9cbf-c5=
2a20add4ed" class=3D"intrnllnk">example</a></p><div class=3D"code_responsiv=
e"><p><span id=3D"d126e305993" itemprop=3D"syntax"><code class=3D"synopsis"=
>sliceViewer(<a href=3D"https://ww2.mathworks.cn/help/releases/R2023b/image=
s/ref/sliceviewer.html#mw_11950457-f539-48a5-9ac6-f24dd5a19393" class=3D"in=
trnllnk"><code class=3D"argument">V</code></a>)</code></span> displays the =
grayscale or RGB
          volume <code class=3D"argument">V</code> in a figure. The figure =
includes a slider that you can use
          to view individual slices of the volume.</p></div></div><div clas=
s=3D"description_element"><div class=3D"code_responsive"><p><span id=3D"d12=
6e306009" itemprop=3D"syntax"><code class=3D"synopsis">sliceViewer(<span cl=
ass=3D"argument_placeholder">___</span>,<code class=3D"argument">Name,Value=
</code>)</code></span> sets
            <a href=3D"https://ww2.mathworks.cn/help/releases/R2023b/images=
/ref/sliceviewer.html#mw_628044a7-9e6d-45fb-bf10-aa4352e11fba" class=3D"int=
rnllnk">properties</a> using
          name-value pair arguments. You can specify multiple name-value pa=
irs. Enclose each
          property name in single quotes.</p><p><span class=3D"example_desc=
"><strong>Example: </strong><code class=3D"literal">sliceViewer(V,'Colormap=
',cmap)</code> creates a
            <code class=3D"object">sliceViewer</code> object and specifies =
the colormap used to display the
          volume. </span></p></div></div><div class=3D"description_element"=
><div class=3D"code_responsive"><p><span id=3D"d126e306031" itemprop=3D"syn=
tax"><code class=3D"synopsis">sv =3D sliceViewer(<span class=3D"argument_pl=
aceholder">___</span>)</code></span> returns a
            <code class=3D"literal">sliceViewer</code> object, <code class=
=3D"argument">sv</code>, with properties that can
          be used to control visualization of the volume. Use input argumen=
ts from any of the
          previous syntaxes.</p></div></div></div><div class=3D"alert alert=
-info"><span class=3D"alert_icon icon-alert-info-reverse"></span><p class=
=3D"alert_heading"><strong>Note</strong></p><p>Medical Imaging Toolbox=E2=
=84=A2 extends the functionality of the <code class=3D"object">sliceViewer<=
/code> (Image Processing Toolbox=E2=84=A2) object to display the slices of =
a <a href=3D"https://ww2.mathworks.cn/help/releases/R2023b/medical-imaging/=
ref/medicalvolume.html"><code class=3D"object">medicalVolume</code></a><spa=
n role=3D"cross_prod"> (Medical Imaging Toolbox)</span>
          object. For more information, see <a href=3D"https://ww2.mathwork=
s.cn/help/releases/R2023b/medical-imaging/ref/sliceviewer.html"><code class=
=3D"object">sliceViewer</code></a><span role=3D"cross_prod"> (Medical Imagi=
ng Toolbox)</span>.</p></div></div><div class=3D"ref_sect"><h3 id=3D"mw_4bc=
